$ /sys

The → Linux/filesystem/sysfs filesystem is *the* filesystem to export kernel objects (→ Linux/kernel/kobject). It is usually mounted on `/sys`. It contains information about
→ Linux/block-device[block devices] (→ Linux/fhs/sys/block) and other kernel stuff.

Every registered → Linux/kernel/kobject creates a directory in or under `/sys`.

The sysfs needs the `CONFIG_SYSFS` configuration option.

sa:

  → Linux/fhs/sys/bus contains a flat directory layout of the bus types in the → Linux/kernel.
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/class
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/dev
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/devices contains representation of the device tree.
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/firmware
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/fs contains subdirectories for some → Linux/filesystem[filesystems].
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/kernel
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/module
    -
  → Linux/fhs/sys/power

